      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — centrifugal pump impeller domain",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) study performed on three systematically refined meshes (4.2M, 12.6M, 37.8M elements). GCI for hemolysis index QoI at design point: 3.1%. Extrapolated value within 1.4% of finest mesh prediction. Discretization error contribution to total uncertainty budget confirmed acceptable for MRL 5.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2026-03-14T09:22:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-cou2-experimental-hemolysis",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental hemolysis index validation — 5 operating conditions",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements across 5 flow-speed combinations (3 L/min at 2400 RPM through 6 L/min at 3200 RPM). Mean absolute relative error: 18.7%. All predictions within two standard deviations of experimental scatter. Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition uncertainty (±5%) yields 95th-percentile NIH band fully below clinical threshold of 0.005 g/100 L. Validation data sourced from FDA benchmark repository.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2026-03-14T11:47:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-cou2-monte-carlo-uq",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification — hemolysis prediction envelope",
      "description": "10,000-sample Monte Carlo analysis propagating uncertainties in: blood viscosity (±8%), pump rotational speed (±0.5%), inlet flow rate (±3%), and power-law hemolysis model coefficients (±15%). 95th-percentile NIH across all operating conditions: 0.00312 g/100 L, remaining below the 0.005 g/100 L clinical threshold. Sensitivity indices confirm hemolysis model coefficient uncertainty dominates (Sobol first-order index 0.61). This evidence item was finalized and timestamped following cryptographic signing of the package due to a post-signature QC review cycle, introducing a minor temporal inconsistency.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2026-03-14T14:03:00Z"
    }
