    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps relative to MRL 5 requirements, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo UQ demonstrates 95th-percentile NIH predictions remain below the absolute clinical threshold of 0.005 g/100 L across all assessed operating conditions, and that identified gaps are bounded by conservative assumptions. Remaining epistemic gaps (test samples, equivalency of inputs) are flagged for resolution in the next design iteration. Acceptance is conditional on submission of supplementary inter-unit variability data prior to IDE submission.",
